name: Toronto Birth Centre
directions: 2nd floor office neutral washrooms and lounge area is assessable by elevator, and available during business hours. If main door is locked (5pm to 8am) ring intercom button to the right of the door to reach a Birth Centre Aide in the main floor birth facility.
comment: Birth Centre Aides may not always be available to let folks in after hours if they are on sleep relief or attending to a birth. The TBC is a safe space supporting midwifery lead birth services for all pregnant people and their families/support people.

name: Half Price Books
directions: Adjoining the attached business Cafe Calypso

name: Parker River National Wildlife Refuge
directions: At Parking Lot 1 on the Refuge
comment: Family restroom, single room

name: USDA Service Center
comment: Two single bathrooms.

name: Plummer Park
directions: There are designated gender neutral restrooms both in the Community Center building (accessible from the outside, without going into the community center itself) and in the building by the tennis courts, closer to Fountain Ave.
comment: These are restrooms in a public park, so they're not always the cleanest or nicest restrooms, but they are explicitly designated as gender-neutral.

name: Cooper Hewitt, Smithsonian Design Museum
directions: Enter thru the garden on 90th street or thru the museum to the cafe. Exit the cafe for two single use gender neutral bathrooms.
comment: Can just walk in thru garden entrance during open hours

name: The Minneapolis College of Art and Design
directions: There are two single-stall, accessible restrooms near the library in the Morrison building, as well as all-gender multi-stall restrooms on the 3rd floor of the main building
comment: MCAD buildings are open to the public during gallery hours, 9am-8pm Monday-Friday, 9am-5pm on Saturday, and 9am-12pm on Sunday.

name: The Cedar Cultural Center
comment: Only available to show-goers

name: Loyola University Stritch School of Medicine
directions: 4th floor

name: Taper Hall of Humanities 1st floor (north end)
directions: Located in the lobby area of the north end of the building, 1st floor.
comment: Can not enter campus without showing USC ID between 9pm and 6am -- all other times is open to the public.

name: Flix Brewhouse
directions: It is next to the two gendered bathrooms
comment: It's a Family Restroom

name: Starbucks Drive-Thru
directions: Street side of the building, near thr patio
comment: A code is necessary to use it. Most recent code is 20201, but is subject to change

name: Grounds for Celebration - Windsor Heights
comment: It doesn't say you have to be a paying customer, but the place is pretty small and you have to walk past the cashier/order counter to access the restroom.

name: Grounds for Celebration - Beaverdale
comment: It doesn't say you have to be a paying customer, but the place is small and you have to walk by the cashier/order counter to access the restroom.

name: Target
directions: The Target is part of the Merle Hay Mall

name: Hillsborough Community College
directions: In building labeled DHUM (humanities building), ground floor. From the entrance facing the south parking lot, it's the door on the right, just after the hallway.
comment: It's a community college campus, so act like a student or an administrator. Parking is free.

name: Trader Joe's
directions: In the back near the free samples and dairy

name: kirklands
directions: Back of building, through a door underneath the exit sign
comment: No need to be a paying customer, please ask associate at cash register If you have trouble finding it.

name: Davidson Hall
directions: On the 1st floor (half basement), on the north end (new side) of the building, near the tunnel.
comment: Accessible, but requires an elevator ride for 3 steps. Building is usually closed to the public after 9 PM and on holidays. Two unisex single stalls.

name: First Unitarian Church of Des Moines
directions: Next to the women's restroom on the main floor
comment: The bathroom is only open when the church itself is open

name: Yesteryears Brewery
directions: Towards the back

name: Steel String Brewery
directions: In the back

name: Mr. Green Bubble Boba Tea
directions: In the back

name: Oakland public Library - Rockridge branch
directions: In the entrance lobby on the right.
comment: Go to the circulation desk and ask for the key to whichever restroom you would prefer to use. This library is in general a really welcoming place for trans/nonbinary people

name: Cactus Taqueria
directions: All the way in the back up the ramp
comment: They go on and off with having a key for the restrooms. At the moment, I think you don't need to get the key.

name: Bowdoin College - Smith Union
directions: The doors to the union are right behind the statue of a polar bear. Just walk into the union and it's in the hall on the right just after the stairs.

name: Goddess and Grocer
directions: Upstairs

name: Goddess and Grocer
directions: In the back, behind the dividing wall.

name: B Star Restaurant
directions: Coming in from the entrance, they are both past the bar on your right. There are two single stall unisex bathrooms.
comment: Paying customers only. Hallway a bit crowded if you have lots of bags on your wheelchair, but doable.

name: Pescado's Burritos
directions: 1st floor, short hallway behind the drink station.
comment: The business owners put up a sign after NC HB2 making both their bathrooms for anyone. Went viral for a little while. I live in Brevard, the sign is still there as of 11/10/16.

name: 574 Boston Ave (Tufts Physics and OT Building)
comment: Enter through the lobby. The doors facing Harvard St are usually locked, but the ones along Boston Ave are usually open.

name: America's Incredible Pizza Company
directions: "Family" individual restroom is across from the salad bar at the back.
comment: You have to either buy a buffet or a $10 game card to enter.

name: Missoula YWCA
comment: Ask if you can use the restroom.

name: University of California Office of the President
directions: The restroom is located in the lobby, immediately to the left as you enter through Franklin Street entrance, next to the "Lobby 1" meeting room.
comment: The restroom is located outside of the secured office area; no badge or pass is needed to access it.

name: Rudie's Seafood and Sausage
directions: Two Bathrooms on Premises
comment: Probably have to be a paying customer, but you act like you're going to the bar. Doubt they would care!

name: Taper Hall (University of Southern California)
directions: On the ground floor next to the water fountain by THH101 and THH102

name: Maple Leaf Ace Hardware & Paint
directions: Back corner-- turn right at the cashiers and left at the next wall.
comment: Ask for an employee to unlock; you do not need to be a paying customer.

name: Evanston Township High School
directions: third floor in the art wing
comment: For students.

name: Charlie Palmer Steak
directions: On E 54th St on 5th Ave, north side of street. it is immediately to your left once you enter the front door. Door says "Ladies/Gents" but it's one unisex room.
comment: Walk in and tell the host you think you are meeting someone at the bar. Take a look around the bar. Then ask where the restroom is.

name: Penn Graduate School of Education
directions: Enter the building, show an ID, and walk toward the center of the building. You'll find the accessible/gender-neutral restroom on the first floor next to the elevator.

name: Bayshore Shopping Centre
directions: 2nd floor, at the back of the food court
comment: Two separate single stall bathrooms. Sign states that they are for families with small children, however nothing is enforcing this. Equipped with regular and child sized toilets and changing table.

name: Engemann Student Health Center
directions: 100% sure there are on the second floor, haven't checked on other floors.
comment: Open to the public

name: Walter Payton College Prep HS
directions: First floor by wester entrance, to the right.
comment: Ask the security guards for directions; they're generally accommodating.

name: EN
directions: Through the front door, head to the right toward the bar and the bathroom hallway is on the left toward the end of the bar.
comment: Just walk right in, if questioned, say you're meeting a friend but they aren't there yet.

name: Small World Coffee Witherspoon
directions: one on the right just past the register, a few more in the hallway in the back (on the left)
comment: gender neutral single rooms

name: Jammin Crepes
directions: in the back, on the right across from the coat hooks
comment: Two gender neutral large lovely single rooms

name: Hostelling International Richmond
directions: First floor across from the front desk. Front door has a small stairwell and is locked from 11PM-7AM, back door entrance has a lift but is locked at all times.
comment: It's a nonprofit 24 hour hotel/accomodations, but the bathroom is primarily for guests and community participants of the organizations activities. Talk to the person at the front desk. They have a mission statement that is inclusive to all people regardless of gender, age, race, etc.

name: Minneapolis College of Art and Design
directions: In Morrison (white) building, at the west end of the building (across from the library). In the main building, at the north end of the Third Floor.

name: Museum of Comparative Zoology at Harvard University
directions: Basement level, enter via museum side door (by ramp next to green)
comment: Side door is open to public, no museum admission required

name: HOPE United Church of Christ
directions: Two gender neutral, single person, restrooms.
comment: The church is typically open Sundays from 8a-12p and Tuesday-Thursday 9a-2p.  If you're in the area and need a safe place to relieve yourself, please feel welcome to use our facility.

name: Seattle University, Casey Building
directions: Located at the Broadway side of campus, behind Broadway and Marion streetcar stop, restrooms on each floor of the building are single occupant unisex/gender neutral. Enter the double doors, water fountain and restroom are on the left hand side immediately as you turn in. Stairs and elevators are available to access other floors.
comment: Fifth floor is slightly less public since it hosts multiple conference rooms, but you shouldn't have a problem accessing it.

name: Gray Owl Coffee
directions: At the back of the coffee shop; two single stall bathrooms
comment: Paying customers preferred, but staff is fairly friendly and is unlikely to say anything to you if you go to the back & act like you know where you're going

name: The LGBTQ Center Long Beach
directions: Gender neutral single occupancy bathrooms are available on the 2nd floor. Please check-in with the front desk to access that floor.

name: Gimme! Coffee
directions: In the back, past the register
comment: For customers only

name: Valley Cities Behavioral Health
directions: Two gender neutral bathrooms in lobby, come in front door and go to the right (around corner).

name: University of Chicago
directions: Basement of saieh hall

name: University of Chicago
directions: Third floor, 3 right by harper cafe, 1 across the reading room into weibolt

name: Trinity United Methodist Church
directions: Two upstairs bathrooms that are single person. One downstairs, accessible bathroom that is single person (use lift to access).
comment: The building is always open Sunday mornings (usually 9-2ish). During the week, there are often people around on Tuesday and Thursday mornings and other times as well. Ring the doorbell on the side of the building and ask if you can use a bathroom.

name: Haverford Area YMCA
directions: Two unisex bathrooms are located in the lobby of this Y - one near the windows overlooking the pool area, and one tucked behind the vending machines.
comment: These restrooms are located before the member check-in area, so you don't even need to be a member to use them.

name: Menchies
directions: Back of the store past the cash down a small corridor.
comment: Doesn't appear to be any restrictions. No signs and no one stopped us from using without paying. The staff was really polite.

name: Mex 1 Coastal Cantina
directions: Located in the back of the restaurant. Easily accessible by a back door directly off a parking lot. Follow drive to rear of the building.
comment: Friendly waitstaff and two stalls. If you enter through the back door, you won't have to speak with anyone.

name: Cloud 9 Tea House
directions: In the hallway to the right of the entrance.

name: Sun Liquor Lounge
comment: 21+. Paying customers preferably, but it never hurts to ask nicely

name: Sun Liquor Distillery
directions: Right hand side to the back
comment: Preferably for paying customers, but if you ask nicely staff will let anyone use restrooms

name: Piccolo Pronto
directions: Restrooms in this restaurant are to the far right as you enter, toward the back.

name: Embassy Suites North DFW
directions: First floor, around the corner past the elevators
comment: You can definitely park, walk in, use this restroom and leave without anyone noticing you are not a guest.  Parking is not monitored.

name: Oxford University Press
directions: Go through the front door, to the left of the reception desk. Restroom is to the left of the door that leads to the elevator lobby.
comment: Typically, the people at the reception desk will allow non-employees to use the restroom, but unfortunately it's not guaranteed.

name: Caffe Bene
directions: In the back of the cafe, next to the seating area
comment: You have to buy something in order to get the restroom code

name: Lyric Cinema Cafe
directions: Through the main doors and down the corridor to the left.

name: Environmental Center
directions: Main floor and second floor
comment: The building is accessible to everyone during work hours and can be accessed by students 24/7.

name: Montserrat College of Art
directions: First Floor, to the back of the building, down a hallway on the right as you pass through the Schlosberg gallery
comment: Our main gallery and the Schlosberg Gallery (hallway gallery) are open to the public. You'll find a safe place to use the facilities & some art to boot!

name: YWCA Pierce County
directions: First floor
comment: You must be a YWCA client or staff member to use.  Community members can also request tours and can use the bathrooms.

name: Papilles
directions: The bathrooms are in the backroom on the right hand side. There are two single gender neutral stalls!
comment: This caf is pretty small, so you might have to be a paying customer.

name: Everybody Reads Books and Stuff
directions: In the back, near the community meeting room

name: Luther Seminary
directions: 2nd floor at the top of the stairs next to the seminaryry pastors office.
comment: Building is open 8-5 on weekdays, intermittently on weekends.

name: Planet Labs
directions: Esconde floor
comment: You need to be an employee at Planet.

name: Book Soup
directions: straight back from Sunset Blvd. entrance
comment: very trans-friendly environment!!! no need to buy anything.

name: The Strawberry Patch
directions: In the back left of the business
comment: Single stall with a gender inclusive sign over the door.  Owner is polite.

name: Cinemark at Market Heights
directions: On either side where the numbered theatres are.
comment: Gender neutral, single, family restroom.

name: Joe Coffee
directions: Back of the main seating area, to the right

name: Harvard Law School, Wasserstein Hall
directions: In the basement, right by the stairwell/elevator that is located near the entrance closet to Pound Hall.
comment: Locked at night and sometimes on weekends but accessible to general public during the school day.

name: 2nd Story Brewing Company
directions: Back of the restaurant to the left, arrowed sign.
comment: Ask for the restroom they will point you towards the back where it's located. Do not have to be a paying customer.

name: New Leaf Community Markets
directions: in back of store opposite Pacific Ave. Go into the back room by the beer section, down the hallway, on the left side.
comment: Must get a bathroom token for the lock from cashiers at the front but a dime will also fit and open the door. Single room so you may need to wait in the hallway or near the door if someone is in there already

name: La Montaita Co-op
directions: Down hallway to the left of the registers (if entering store)

name: Greenlight Bookstore
comment: You need to ask for the key at the front desk, but otherwise there are no restrictions on bathroom use.

name: University of Missouri Math Science Building
directions: Third floor near the elevator
comment: Single occupancy restroom

name: Innis College
directions: Washrooms on the second and third floor on the eastern wing of the building. Elevators is towards the back of the building. Automatic doors at the St George street entrance.
comment: It's a university building but ID is not required to enter

name: Extracto Coffee
directions: 2 single-use restrooms all the way in the back.
comment: You'd probably have to buy something to avoid getting the side-eye, but their coffee is delicious!

name: Target Lino Lakes
directions: On the right side of the pharmacy counter
comment: It's a "Family Restroom" by the pharmacy - but is a single room and the door locks

name: Extracto
directions: All the way in the back- there are 2 single-use gender neutral bathrooms!
comment: You'd probably have to buy something to avoid getting the side eye, but they have fantastic coffee!
